<div class="body-container">
	<div class="inner-content" id="section2">
		<center>
			<h1>ICE911 Case Study</h1>
			<hr>
		</center>
		<div class="container inner-content-container">
			<p>ICE911, a not-for-profit organization, specializing in
				studying the melting rate of glaciers and protecting the glacial ice
				melt collected weather and temperature data across various lakes and
				glaciers through a serious of strategically placed Industrial IoT
				sensors. The collected data was transmitted in a compressed form
				over SMS.</p>
			<br> <br>
			<p>
				<b>Challenge:</b>
			</p>
			<li>Monitor the polar sensors (pressure, voltage and
				temperature)
			<li>Transmitting data streamed from extreme terrains with
				limited connectivity
			<li>Gathering and staging the streamed time series IoT data from
				multiple sensors
			<li>Analyze, Model and visualize the data <br> <br>
				<p>
					<b>Technology Stack:</b>
				</p>
				<p>Amazon AWS [Lambda, Cloudwatch],Python, PHP, InfluxDB,
					Grafana</p> <br>
				<p>
					<img src="assets/images/ICE911.png" height="80%" width="100%">
				</p> <br>
				<p>
					<b>Solution:</b>
				</p>
			<li>Setup, configure and deploy AWS Lambda components to fetch
				data streamed through SMS
			<li>AWS components to curate data and stream to a structured
				time series database on InfluxDB
			<li>Present data through a secure Grafana system
			<li>Outage monitors and alerts system with AWS cloud watch <br>
			<br>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>
